---
headerTitle: Find an apprenticeship
---
<div class="hgroup">
  <h1 class="heading-xlarge">Contact us</h1>
</div>
<div class="grid-wrapper">
  <div class="grid grid-2-3">

    <section class="controls-3-4">
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="contactName" class="form-label">Full name</label>
        <input type="text" id="contactName" class="form-control">
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="contactEmail" class="form-label">Email address</label>
        <input type="email" id="contactEmail" class="form-control">
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="contactSubject" class="form-label">Briefly describe your question</label>
        <select name="" id="" class="hide-nojs small-btm-margin select-inject">
          <option value="noSelect">-- Or choose from one of these questions --</option>
          <option value="changeEmail">I need to change my email address</option>
          <option value="forgottenEmailAddress">I’ve forgotten my email address</option>
          <option value="cantSignIn">I can't sign in to my account</option>
          <option value="activationHelp">I can't activate my account</option>
          <option value="">I'd like to know more about eligibility and funding</option>
          <option value="">I'm having problems submitting my application</option>
          <option value="">I can't see my application</option>
          <option value="">I want to withdraw an application</option>
          <option value="">I want to delete my account</option>
        </select>
        <div id="changeEmail" class="selfServe panel-indent toggle-content hide-nojs text">
          If you'd like to change your email address visit the <a href="change-email.html">update email</a> page. If you're still having problems contact us using this form.
        </div>

        <div id="forgottenEmailAddress" class="selfServe panel-indent toggle-content hide-nojs text">
          <p>If you've forgotten your email address, visit the <a href="profile-noaccess.html">forgotten password</a> page. If you're still having problems contact us using this form.</p>
        </div>

        <div id="activationHelp" class="selfServe panel-indent toggle-content hide-nojs text">
          <p><a href="profile-success.html">Activate your account</a> by signing in. You'll need the email address and password you used to create your account.</p>
          <p>If you haven't received your activation code, you can re-send it from the activation page. Make sure you've checked your junk email folder.</p>
          <p>If you're still having problems contact us using this form.</p>
        </div>

        <div id="cantSignIn" class="selfServe panel-indent toggle-content hide-nojs text">
          <p>If you're having trouble signing in to your account, visit the <a href="profile-noaccess.html">forgotten password</a> page. If you're still having problems contact us using this form.</p>
        </div>
        <input type="text" class="form-control select-injected" id="contactSubject">
      </div>


      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="contactQuery" class="form-label">More details about your question (optional)</label>
        <textarea name="" id="contactQuery" rows="4" class="form-control"></textarea>
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <a href="#" class="button">Send</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="text">
      <h2 class="heading-medium">Apprenticeship helpline</h2>

<!--       <p>Contact the helpline if you’d prefer to speak to somebody, or if you're having difficulty with the contact form.</p> -->

      <p class="small-btm-margin">Telephone (free): 0800 015 0400</p>
      <p>Telephone (from mobiles): 02476 826482</p>

      <p>Email: <a href="mailto:nationalhelpdesk@findapprenticeship.service.gov.uk">nationalhelpdesk@findapprenticeship.service.gov.uk</a></p>

      <p>Contact the <a href="https://nationalcareersservice.direct.gov.uk/Pages/Home.aspx" rel="external">National Careers Service</a> if you're wondering whether an apprenticeship is right for you.</p>
    </section>

  </div>

</div>